DRY VERMOUTHS

The predominant use of dry Vermouth is in the dry Martini. Now it has become fashionable (particularly for those who want to lose weight) to drink it straight over the rocks with a twist of lemon peel. Another popular drink is simply to add a teaspoon of Cassis and

some ice cubes, thus creating the much appreciated ‘Vermouth Cassis.’
